                     <note>
                        <p>Delhi Persian 937 b. 
</p>
                        <p>Opening part of the <title key="work_20476">Kīmiyā-yi saʿādat</title> by <persName key="viaf_31996761" role="aut">al-Ghazālī</persName>, comprising the preface (f. 11v), extensive introduction (f. 14v), and the first rukn (f. 57v). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Ornamental frontispiece at the beginning. 
</p>
                        <p>The beginning of the first rukn is indicated by an ornamental device added in margin (f. 57v), probably dating from the period the list of contents (item a) was added. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 109v): completed in mid Muḥarram 914/late May 1508. 
</p>
                        <p>Substantive inscription along right margin of folio 11v erased. 
</p>
